<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFWilson.2C_Edward_Raymond2000">Wilson, Edward Raymond (2000). <i>Sociobiology: the new synthesis</i>. Cambridge: Belknap Press of Harvard University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0674000897" class="internal">ISBN 0-674-00089-7</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Sociobiology%3A+the+new+synthesis&amp;rft.aulast=Wilson%2C+Edward+Raymond&amp;rft.au=Wilson%2C+Edward+Raymond&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.place=Cambridge&amp;rft.pub=Belknap+Press+of+Harvard+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-674-00089-7&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Evolutionary_psychology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFWright.2C_Robert_C._M.1995">Wright, Robert C. M. (1995). <i>The moral animal: evolutionary psychology and everyday life</i>. New York: Vintage Books. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0679763996" class="internal">ISBN 0-679-76399-6</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+moral+animal%3A+evolutionary+psychology+and+everyday+life&amp;rft.aulast=Wright%2C+Robert+C.+M.&amp;rft.au=Wright%2C+Robert+C.+M.&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Vintage+Books&amp;rft.isbn=0-679-76399-6&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Evolutionary_psychology"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
